FBIS4-33507 "drlat109_a_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-109 Daily Report 6 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Border Guards Deny Attack on Refugee Vessel Border Guards Deny Attack on Refugee Vessel PA0606202294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1820 GMT 6 May 94 PA0606202294 Mexico City NOTIMEX Spanish BFN [Text] Havana, 6 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Border Guards Unit refrained from attacking a vessel on which 61 persons fled the island last weekend, a government source said today. The guards, who had sighted minors aboard, limited themselves to escorting the vessel until it had left Cuban jurisdictional waters. The U.S. Coast Guard rescued the vessel on Saturday in international waters off the Florida Keys; there were seven wounded aboard. The Cuban Foreign Ministry refused to comment on the incident.
